<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE> Law Teachers in the Department of Land Economy</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H1><IMG SRC="/GIFS/SHIELD.GIF" ALIGN = MIDDLE>Law Teachers in the Department of Land Economy, with their research interests</H1>

<BR>
<STRONG>M. J. Dixon</STRONG>, M.A. (Oxon.); Robinson College; University Assistant Lecturer.  Land law: co-ownership.  International law: use of force; sources of law; relationship with municipal law.
<HR>
<STRONG>M. J. Grant</STRONG>, LL.D. (Otago); Hon. MRTPI; Barrister and Solicitor (New Zealand);  Clare College; Professor of Land Economy, Head of Department.  Planning law and land policy.  Environmental law.  Property law.  Local government, finance and structure.
<HR>
<STRONG>D. R. Howarth</STRONG>, M.A. (Cantab.), LL.M., M.Phil. (Yale); Clare College; University Lecturer.  Law of negligence.  Economic analysis of law.  Jurisprudence.
<HR>
<STRONG>P. G. McHugh</STRONG>, LL.B. (Vict.), LL.M. (Sask.), Ph.D. (Cantab.); Sidney Sussex College; University Lecturer.  Colonial constitutional law and history: aboriginal peoples' rights.  Constitutional theory.  Land law.
<HR>
<HR>
Address of the Department: 19 Silver Street, Cambridge CB3 9EP.  (Tel: 01223-337147.  Fax: 01223-337130.)

