   <TITLE></TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.01Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="wall.jpg">

<H1><IMG SRC="earthani.gif" HSPACE=15 VSPACE=15 HEIGHT=64 WIDTH=64 ALIGN=ABSCENTER><FONT SIZE=+2>R</FONT><FONT SIZE=+1>CIL
</FONT><FONT SIZE=+2>A</FONT><FONT SIZE=+1>LUMNI </FONT><FONT SIZE=+2>N</FONT><FONT SIZE=+1>EWS</FONT></H1>

<P>
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><FONT SIZE=+2>W</FONT>e want to keep in touch with the many RCIL alumni
dispersed around the globe. This section features regular updates on alumni
events and contributions from alumni on recent personal and professional
developments.</P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P>
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P>

<H3>Index</H3>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<LI><A HREF="#Alumni Events">Alumni Events</A></LI>

<LI><A HREF="#Alumni News">Alumni Profiles</A></LI>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P>
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P>

<H3><A NAME="Alumni Events"></A><B>Alumni Events</B></H3>

<UL>
<H3><IMG SRC="ball.gif" HSPACE=5 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10><B><FONT SIZE=+0>Michaelmas
Term 1996</FONT></B></H3>
</UL>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><FONT SIZE=+2>T</FONT>he Centre's annual alumni reception was held on
29 September, hosted by the new directors John Dugard and James Crawford.
Current members discussed their latest projects and answered questions
from guests on a variety of topics of current interest in international
law. The occasion was an excellent opportunity for visitors to view the
nearly completed extension, and was characterised by all as a great success.</P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<P>
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P>

<H3><A NAME="Alumni News"></A>Alumni Profile</H3>

<UL>
<H3><IMG SRC="ball.gif" HSPACE=5 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10><FONT SIZE=+0>David
Lazerwitz </FONT></H3>
</UL>

<UL>
<UL>
<P>David <FONT SIZE=+0>(Snyder Scholar 1995) </FONT>is currently serving
as a law clerk in the US Court of Appeals for the Tenth Circuit in Oklahoma.
In September 1997, after a well-deserved break in South America, he will
join the natural resources practice group of the Denver, Colorado firm
of Holland &amp; Hart. His latest article entitled &quot;The Application
and Limits of International Law in Resolving Transboundary Water Resources
Conflicts&quot; and dealing with the issue of groundwater and the Israeli-Palestinian
peace process, is soon to be published in the Indiana Law Review.</P>
</UL>
</UL>

<P>
<HR WIDTH="100%"></P>

