<H1>Foreword</H1>
<PRE>
Welcome to the future!  Lawyers Cooperative Publishing is pleased to present 
the Fall 1995 edition of <i>The Legal List</i>, by Erik J. Heels.

The past six months have seen vast changes in the way the Internet community 
deals with the expansive amount of knowledge available on the Internet.  
Content directories, such as Lycos (http://www.lycos.com) and Yahoo 
(http://www.yahoo.com), have consistently been among the busiest sites on the 
Internet.  In fact, the Internet has become so big that it is almost 
impossible to find anything unless a good content directory is used.  We at 
Thomson Legal Publishing are proud that LCP recognized this fact, and that LCP 
was the first legal publisher to address this vital need of the legal research 
community with <i>The Legal List</i>.

The overwhelming success of our first print edition of <i>The Legal List</i>, 
along with the continuing success of our online version at the LCP World Wide 
Web site (http://www.lcp.com), shows that the legal community appreciates the 
resource.  We've also expanded our e-mail offerings to keep our clients 
informed about new legal resources on the Net.  To automatically receive 
<i>The Legal List</i> updates by e-mail, send a message to 
listserv@listserv.lcp.com with the following line in the body of the message: 
subscribe TLL-announce <i>your name</i> ("your name" should be your real name) 

As always, for additional information on LCP Internet resources, send e-mail 
to info@lcp.com.  See you on the Net!

Max Kelly
Director of Core Technology
Thomson Legal Publishing
max@lcp.com



</PRE>
