2.1.2.10.  Department of State.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
Department of State
2201 C Street NW
Washington, DC  20520
Phone:  202-647-4000

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Department of State advises the President in the formulation and execution 
of foreign policy.  Department of State agencies include the Agency for 
International Development, Arms Control and Disarmament Agency, Foreign 
Service Institute, United States Information Agency, and the United States 
Mission to the United Nations.

Domain:  dosaopr.gov

2.1.2.11.  Department of the Interior.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
As the Nation's principal conservation agency, the Department of the Interior 
has responsibility for most of our nationally-owned public lands and natural 
resources.  Established by the act of Mar. 3, 1949 (43 USCS 1451) (1849).  
Department of Interior agencies include the Bureau of Land Management, Bureau 
of Reclamation, Minerals Management Service, National Biological Survey, 
National Park Service, Office of Surface Mining Reclamation and Enforcement;, 
United States Bureau of Mines, United States Fish and Wildlife Service, and 
the United States Geological Survey.

Domain:  doi.gov
WWW:  http://info.er.usgs.gov/doi/doi.html

2.1.2.12.  Department of the Treasury.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Department of the Treasury performs four basic functions:  formulating and 
recommending economic, financial, tax, and fiscal policies; serving as 
financial agent for the United States Government; enforcing the law; and 
manufacturing coins and currency.  Established the act of Sep. 2, 1789 (31 
USCS 1001) (1789).  Department of the Treasury agencies include the Bureau of 
Alcohol Tobacco and Firearms, Bureau of Engraving and Printing, Bureau of the 
Public Debt, Federal Law Enforcement Training Center, Financial Management 
Service, Internal Revenue Service, Office of the Comptroller of the Currency, 
Office of Thrift Supervision, United States Customs Service, United States 
Mint, and the United States Secret Service.

Domain:  ustreas.gov
WWW:  http://www.ustreas.gov

2.1.2.13.  Department of Transportation.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Department of Transportation establishes the Nation's overall 
transportation policy.  Established by the act of Oct. 15, 1966 (49 USCS app. 
1651 note) (1966).  DOT agencies include the Bureau of Transportation 
Statistics, Federal Aviation Administration, Federal Highway Administration, 
Federal Highway Traffic Safety Administration, Federal Railroad 
Administration, Federal Transit Administration, Maritime Administration, 
Research and Special Programs Administration, Saint Lawrence Seaway 
Development Corporation, and the United States Coast Guard.

Domain:  dot.gov
WWW:  http://www.dot.gov
Gopher:  gopher://gopher.dot.gov

2.1.2.14.  Department of Veterans Affairs.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Department of Veterans Affairs operates programs to benefit veterans and 
members of their families.  Established by Executive Order 5398 of Jul. 21, 
1930, in accordance with the act of Jul. 3, 1930 (46 Stat. 1016) (1930).  
Established as a department by the Department of Veterans Affairs Act (38 USCS 
201 note).

Domain:  va.gov
WWW:  http://www.va.gov

