Phone:  202-376-8177

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Commission on Civil Rights collects and studies information on 
discrimination or denials of equal protection of the laws because of race, 
color, religion, sex, age, handicap, or national origin.  Established by the 
Civil Rights Act of 1957 and reestablished by the United States Commission of 
