2.1.3.13.  Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation promotes and preserves public 
confidence in banks and protects the money supply by providing insurance 
coverage for bank deposits and periodic examinations of insured State-
chartered banks that are not members of the Federal Reserve System.  
Established by the Federal Reserve Act, as amended (12 USCS 1811 et seq.) 
(1933).

Domain:  fdic.gov
