SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Federal Election Commission exercises exclusive jurisdiction in the 
administration and civil enforcement of laws regulating the acquisition and 
expenditure of campaign funds to ensure compliance by participants in the 
Federal election campaign process.  Established by Section 309 of the Federal 
Election Campaign Act of 1971, as amended (2 USCS 437c) (1971).

