unemployment-sickness benefit programs for the Nation's railroad workers and 
their families.  Established by the Railroad Retirement Act of 1934, as 
amended (42 USCS 2001-228z-1, 231 et seq.) (1934).  The Board administers the 
Railroad Retirement Act of 1974 (45 USCS 231-231v) and the Railroad 
Unemployment Insurance Act (45 USCS 351-368).

Domain:  None.

2.1.3.49.  Resolution Trust Corporation.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
Resolution Trust Corporation
801 Seventeenth Street NW
Washington, DC  20434
Phone:  202-416-6900

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Resolution Trust Corporation was established to manage and resolve failed 
savings associations that were insured by the Federal Savings and Loan 
Insurance Corporation.  Established on Aug. 9, 1989 by the Financial 
Institutions Reform, Recovery, and Enforcement Act of 1989 (12 USCS 1441a) and 
scheduled to terminate no later than Dec. 31, 1995.

Domain:  rtc.gov

2.1.3.50.  Securities and Exchange Commission.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
Securities and Exchange Commission
450 Fifth Street NW
Washington, DC  20549
Phone:  202-272-3100

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Securities and Exchange Commission administers Federal securities laws 
that seek to provide protection to investors; to ensure that securities 
markets are fair and honest; and, when necessary, to provide the means to 
enforce securities laws through sanctions.  Established by the Securities 
Exchange Act of 1934 (15 USCS 78a-78jj).

Domain:  None.

2.1.3.51.  Selective Service System.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
Selective Service System
National Headquarters
Arlington, VA  22209-2425
Phone:  703-235-2555

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The purpose of the Selective Service System is to be prepared to supply to the 
Armed Forces human resources adequate to ensure the security of the United 
States, with concomitant regard for the maintenance of an effective national 
economy.  Established by the Military Selective Service Act (50 USCS app. 451-
471a).  The authority to induct registrants expired Jul. 1, 1973.

Domain:  None.

2.1.3.52.  Small Business Administration.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
Small Business Administration
409 Third Street SW
Washington, DC  20416
Phone:  202-205-6600; 800-U-ASK-SBA (answer desk)

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The fundamental purposes of the Small Business Administration are to aid, 
counsel, assist, and protect the interests of small business; ensure that 
small business concerns receive a fair portion of Government purchases, 
contracts, and subcontracts, as well as the sales of Government property; 
makes loans to small business concerns, State and local development companies, 
and the victims of floods or other catastrophes, or of certain types of 
economic injury; and license, regulate, and makes loans to small business 
investment companies.  Established by the Small Business Act of 1953, it 
derives its present authority from the Small Business Act (15 USCS 631 et 
seq.).  It also derives authority from the Small Business Investment Act of 
1958 (15 USCS 661 et seq.).

Domain:  sba.gov
WWW:  http://www.sbaonline.sba.gov
Gopher:  gopher://gopher.sbaonline.sba.gov

2.1.3.53.  Tennessee Valley Authority.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
Tennessee Valley Authority
400 West Summit Hill Drive
Knoxville, TN  37902
Phone:  615-632-2101

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Tennessee Valley Authority conducts a unified program of resource 
development (including flood control and electric power production) for the 
advancement of economic growth in the Tennessee Valley region.  Established by 
the act of May 18, 1933 (16 USCS 831-831dd).

Domain:  tva.gov

2.1.3.54.  Thrift Depositor Protection Oversight Board.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
Thrift Depositor Protection Oversight Board
808 Seventeenth Street NW
Washington, DC  20232
Phone:  202-416-2650

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Thrift Depositor Protection Oversight Board is responsible for overseeing 
and monitoring the operations of the Resolution Trust Corporation.  
Established by the Financial Institutions Reform, Recovery, and Enforcement 
Act of 1989 (12 USCS 1441a).

Domain:  None.

2.1.3.55.  Trade and Development Agency.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
Trade and Development Agency
Room 309, State Annex 16
Washington, DC  20523-1602
Phone:  703-875-4357

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Trade and Development Agency's mandate is to promote economic development 
in, and simultaneously export US goods and services to, developing and middle-
income countries.  Established by Section 2202 of the Omnibus Trade and 
Competitiveness Act of 1988 (22 USCS 2421).  Made an independent agency in 
1992 (22 USCS 2421).

Domain:  None.

2.1.3.56.  United States Arms Control and Disarmament Agency.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
United States Arms Control and Disarmament Agency
320 Twenty-First Street NW
Washington, DC  20451
Phone:  202-647-8677

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The United States Arms Control and Disarmament Agency formulates and 
implements arms control and disarmament policies that promote the national 
security of the United States and its relations with other countries.  
Established by the act of Sep. 26, 1961 (22 USCS 2561).

Domain:  None.

2.1.3.57.  United States Information Agency.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The United States Information Agency is responsible for the US Government's 
overseas information and cultural and academic programs, including the Voice 
of America.  Established by the United States Information and Education 
Exchange Act of 1948 (22 USCS 1431) and derives authority from the Mutual 
Educational and Cultural Exchange Act of 1961 (22 USCS 2451).

Domain:  usia.gov
WWW:  http://www.usia.gov
Gopher:  gopher://gopher.usia.gov

2.1.3.58.  United States International Development Cooperation Agency.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
United States International Development Cooperation Agency
320 Twenty-First Street NW
Washington, DC  20523-0001
Phone:  202-647-1850

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The United States International Development Cooperation Agency's function is 
policy planning, policymaking, and policy coordination on international 
economic issues affecting developing countries.  Agencies include the United 
States Agency for International Development (USAID) and the Overseas Private 
Investment Corporation.  Established by Reorganization Plan No. 2 of 1979 (5 
USCS app.).

Domain:  None.

2.1.3.59.  United States International Trade Commission.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The United States International Trade Commission furnishes studies, reports, 
and recommendations involving international trade and tariffs to the 
President, the Congress, and other Government agencies.  Established by the 
act of Sep. 8, 1916 (39 Stat. 795).

Domain:  usitc.gov
WWW:  http://www.usitc.gov
FTP:  ftp://ftp.usitc.gov/pub

2.1.3.60.  United States Postal Service.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The United States Postal Service provides mail processing and delivery 
services to individuals and businesses within the United States.  Established 
as an independent agency by the Postal Reorganization Act (39 USCS 101 et 
seq.) (1970).

Domain:  usps.gov
WWW:  http://www.usps.gov

