<H1>Chapter 2.3.  Legislative Branch.</H1>
<PRE>

2.3.1.  Congress.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Congress of the United States was created by Article 1, Section 1, of the 
Constitution, which was adopted by the Constitutional Convention on Sep. 17, 
1787, and which provided that "All legislative Powers herein granted shall be 
vested in a Congress of the United States, which shall consist of a Senate and 
House of Representative."

2.3.1.1.  Senate.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Senate is composed of 100 Members, two from each State, who are elected 
for a term of six years.

Domain:  senate.gov
Gopher:  gopher://gopher.senate.gov
FTP:  ftp://ftp.senate.gov

2.3.1.2.  House of Representatives.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The House of Representatives comprises 435 Representatives.  The number 
representing each State is determined by population, but every state is 
entitled to at least one Representative.

This site provides bill tracking, voting records, information on the US Code, 
and more.  The House of Representatives Constituent Electronic Mail System is 
a program designed to give  constituents electronic access to their elected 
representatives.  Inclusion of your full name and mailing address will insure 
that your  Member can identify your residence within his or her Congressional  
District.

