Helsinki Commission (Commission on Security and Cooperation in Europe)
234 Ford House Office Building
Washington, DC  20515
CSCE@HR.HOUSE.GOV

2.3.2.  Architect of the Capitol.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Architect of the Capitol is charged with operating and maintaining the 
buildings of the Capitol committed to his care by Congress.  Permanent 
authority for these functions was established by the act of Aug. 15, 1876 (40 
USCS 162, 163).

Domain:  aocnet.gov

2.3.3.  Congressional Budget Office.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Congressional Budget Office provides the Congress with assessments of the 
economic impact of the Federal budget.  Established by the Congressional 
Budget Act of 1974 (2 USCS 601) (USCS).

Domain:  cbo.gov

2.3.4.  General Accounting Office.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The General Accounting Office is the investigative arm of the Congress and is 
charged with examining all matters relating to the receipt and disbursement of 
public funds.  Established by the Budget and Accounting Act of 1921 (31 USCS 
702).

Domain:  gao.gov
E-mail:  mailto:info@www.gao.gov
WWW:  http://www.gao.gov

2.3.5.  Government Printing Office.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Government Printing Office prints, binds, and distributes the publications 
of the Federal Government.  Established by Congressional Joint Resolution 25 
of Jun. 23, 1860.  Its activities are defined by the act of Oct. 22, 1968, as 
amended (44 USCS 101 et seq.).

Domain:  gpo.gov
WWW:  http://www.access.gpo.gov
Telnet:  telnet://federal.bbs.gpo.gov:3001
BBS Phone:  202-512-1387

2.3.6.  Library of Congress.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Library of Congress in the national library of the United States.  
Established by the act of Apr. 24, 1800 (2 Stat. 56) (1800).  Its activities 
are defined by subsequent legislation (2 USCS 131-168d).  The Copyright Office 
is part of the LOC.

Search LOCIS (Library of Congress Information System) via Telnet or WWW.

Domain:  loc.gov
WWW:  http://www.loc.gov
Gopher:  gopher://gopher.loc.gov
Telnet:  telnet://locis.loc.gov

2.3.7.  Office of Technology Assessment.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Office of Technology Assessment reports to the Congress on the scientific 
and technical impact of government policies and proposed legislative 
initiatives.  Established by the Technology Assessment Act of 1972 (2 USCS 
472) (1972).

Domain:  ota.gov
WWW:  http://www.ota.gov
LISTSERV LISTS:
listserv@media.ota.gov

otanews@media.ota.gov (Office of Technology Assessment News)

2.3.8.  United States Botanic Garden.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
Founded in 1820, the United States Botanic Garden is an educational display 
garden.  Annual appropriation was provided by Congress in 1856 (11 Stat. 104 
(1856).

Domain:  None.


