<H1>Chapter 5.  Other Educational Institutions</H1>
<PRE>
SHORT DESCRIPTION:
This chapter contains information about other US educational institutions.  An 
organization in this chapter would most likely have a domain name ending in 
.edu (education).

One of the best ways to find the e-mail address for a particular individual is 
to call that individual.  If you choose to contact the individuals in this 
chapter via e-mail, please keep your e-mail message short and to-the-point.

5.01.  Carnegie-Mellon University - EnviroGopher.

Gopher:  gopher://envirolink.hss.cmu.edu

5.02.  Texas A&M University.

Domain:  tamu.edu
Gopher:  gopher://gopher.tamu.edu/11/.dir/law.dir

5.03.  Tufts University - Multilaterals Project.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
Peter Stott, Director
Multilaterals Project
Fletcher School of Law & Diplomacy

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Multilaterals Project is an experimental program begun at the Fletcher 
School of Law and Diplomacy in Medford, MA, to make available to the Internet 
community the text of a wide variety of multilateral conventions.  The 
conventions are available via anonymous FTP and WWW.

Domain:  tufts.edu
E-mail:  mailto:pstott@emerald.tufts.edu
WWW:  http://www.tufts.edu/departments/fletcher/multilaterals.html
FTP:  ftp://ftp.fletcher.tufts.edu/pub/diplomacy/

5.04.  University of Georgia, The Regents' Global Center.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
Resources related to Eastern Europe and the Newly-Independent States, 
including political information, economic data, trade leads, databases, 
scholarly papers, grant information, and current news.

Domain:  peachnet.edu
Gopher:  gopher://gopher.peachnet.edu
Telnet:  telnet://info:info@info.peachnet.edu

5.05.  University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign - Project Gutenberg.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
Michael S.  Hart
Director, Project Gutenberg 405 West Elm St.
Urbana, IL 61801

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
Project Gutenberg was started in 1971.  Its goal is to release 10,000 books, 
whose US copyrights have expired, by the year 2001.  Project Gutenberg 
requests that you check your own copyright laws for using a file outside the 
United States.  Files are released monthly in ascii text format.  An 
electronic newsletter is also available.  Project Gutenberg requests that the 
FTP server not be used from 10:00 am to 6:00 pm Central Standard Time 
(Daylight in summer) as this is peak usage.

Domain:  uiuc.edu
E-mail:  mailto:dircompg@ux1.cso.uiuc.edu
FTP:  ftp://mrcnext.cso.uiuc.edu/etext/

5.06.  University of Massachusetts.

Domain:  umass.edu
Gopher:  gopher://gopher.ucs.umass.edu/11/academic/law

5.07.  University of Michigan - The Clearinghouse.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
Lou Rosenfeld
University of Michigan
School of Information and Library Studies
403B West Engineering
Ann Arbor, MI 48109-1092

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The goal of the Clearinghouse is to make available Internet subject-
oriented resource guides.  The guides made available by the Clearinghouse have 
been created by various individuals in the Internet community, including 
students in a course co-taught by the administrator of the Clearinghouse at 
the University of Michigan, School of Information and Library Studies.  Well 
over 100 guides (including <i>The Legal List</i>) are maintained at this 
server.  Of particular interest to those interested in foreign affairs is Sam 
Sternberg's Daily News - Free Internet Sources & Information About the Daily 
News Media Globally.  The Daily News gives instructions for accessing news 
from abroad (e.g.  Eastern Europe, Germany, Italy, Finland, Denmark, China, 
Brazil) via the Internet.

Domain:  umich.edu
E-mail:  mailto:lou@umich.edu
Gopher:  gopher://una.hh.lib.umich.edu/11/inetdirs
FTP:  ftp://una.hh.lib.umich.edu/inetdirsstacks/

5.08.  University of Tennessee - Language in the Judicial Process.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
Language in the Judicial Process
B. Dumas & D. Hale
300 McClung Tower
University of Tennessee
Knoxville, TN 37920
Phone:  (615) 974-1322

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The intention of the editors is to maintain a World Wide Web homepage with 
current information of interest to all interested in law and language.

E-mail:  mailto:dumasb@utk.edu,dhale@utk.edu
WWW:  http://hamlet.la.utk.edu

5.09.  University of Virginia - Copyright Law.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
US copyright laws.

Domain:  virginia.edu
Gopher:  gopher://orion.lib.virginia.edu/11/alpha/copyright

5.10.  University of Virginia - EcoGopher.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
Ecological and environmental information.

Domain:  virginia.edu
Gopher:  gopher://ecosys.drdr.virginia.edu


</PRE>
