<H1>  Chapter 8.  Non-US Resources</H1>
<PRE>
SHORT DESCRIPTION:
This chapter contains information about non-US organizations, governments, and 
educational institutions including the United Nations.

One of the best ways to find the e-mail address for a particular individual is 
to call that individual.  If you choose to contact the individuals in this 
chapter via e-mail, please keep your e-mail message short and to-the-point.

8.01.  Australia - Murdoch University.

Domain:  murdoch.edu.au
WWW:  http://www.murdoch.edu.au
Gopher:  gopher://infolib.murdoch.edu.au/11/.ftp/pub/subj/law/

8.02.  Australia - Murdoch University, E Law.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
E Law Editorial Board
Murdoch University School of Law
Murdoch, Western Australia
AUSTRALIA 6150

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
Under the Electronic Journals, Newsletters - Law sub-menu, you will find E Law 
- Murdoch University Electronic Journal of Law and Legal Bytes, a computer law 
journal.  E Law is a peer-reviewed electronic journal edited by the staff and 
students of the School of Law of Murdoch University in Perth, Australia.  E 
Law welcomes contributions in 4 categories: 1) news, non-commercial 
announcements, hints and tips relating to materials on the net of interest to 
the legal community (NetWatch section); 2) materials of current interest such 
as reports and analyses of developments in the law including significant 
recent cases and legislation, and book reviews; 3) scholarly work in progress 
or materials calling for comment such as research notes and excerpts from 
unfinished larger works; 4) completed papers (these submissions will be 
subject to peer review).

Domain:  murdoch.edu.au
E-mail:  mailto:elaw-editors@csuvax1.murdoch.edu.au
Gopher:  gopher://infolib.murdoch.edu.au:70/11/.ftp/pub/subj/law/jnl/elaw
FTP:  ftp://infolib.murdoch.edu.au/pub/subj/law/jnl/elaw

8.03.  Australia - University of Melbourne Law School.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
The Journal of the Australian and New Zealand Societies for Computers & Law
Dan Hunter, Co-editor
University of Melbourne Law School
Parkville VIC 3052
AUSTRALIA

Domain:  unimelb.edu.au
E-mail:  mailto:dah@rumpole.law.unimelb.edu.au

8.04.  Belgium - Antwerp University, UFSIA.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
Antwerp University: UFSIA
Prinsstraat 10
B-2000 Antwerp BELGIUM
Phone:  32/3/220.41.11

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
UFSIA is a university which offers courses in the human sciences like Applied 
Economics and Law.  Together with another university (UIA) we offer a full law 
program.  Our first year in law contains about 460 students.

Domain:  ufsia.ac.be
WWW:  http://www.ufsia.ac.be/index.html
Gopher:  gopher://gopher.ufsia.ac.be

8.05.  Canada - Canadian Institute of Resources Law.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
Canadian Institute of Resources Law
3330 Professional Faculties Building, Block B
University of Calgary
Calgary, Alberta T2N 1N4.
CANADA

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
Resources is the newsletter of the Canadian Institute of Resources Law and is 
available via e-mail.  Published quarterly, the newsletters purpose is to 
provide timely comments on current resources law issues and to give 
information about Institute publications and programs.

E-mail:  mailto:ANNHED@library.lib.usu.edu

8.06.  Canada - Communications Research Centre.

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
This server provides links to, for example, the Senate of Canada, House of 
Commons, and the Supreme Court of Canada.

Domain:  dgbt.doc.ca
WWW:  http://debra.dgbt.doc.ca/opengov/index.html

8.07.  Canada - International Law Students Association, Ottawa Chapter.

E-mail:  mailto:dbell@magmacom.com
WWW:  http://www2.magmacom.com/~dbell/

8.08.  Canada - Law Reform Commission of Nova Scotia.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
Law Reform Commission of Nova Scotia
8th Floor, Garrison Place
1526 Dresden Row
Halifax, Nova Scotia
Canada B3J 2K2
Phone:  (902) 423-2633
Fax:  (902) 423-0222

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
The Law Reform Commission of Nova Scotia is comprised of seven Commissioners, 
an Executive Director and a Legal Research Officer.  The Commissioners, along 
with the Executive Director and Legal Research Officer, are responsible for 
carrying out the work of law reform in the province.  It operates 
independently of government.  Similar law reform organizations operate this 
way in other provinces in Canada.

The Commission has undertaken 8 projects some of which had reached the Final 
Report stage while others are partially concluded.  They cover a large range 
of concerns and areas of law.  One of the projects is a reference from the 
Government of Nova Scotia.  The other projects were chosen from suggestions to 
the Commission by the public, the judiciary and the legal community.

E-mail:  mailto:mmcconne@fox.nstn.ns.ca
WWW:  http://www.cfn.cs.dal.ca/Law/LRC/LRC-Home.html
Telnet:  telnet://guest@cfn.cs.dal.ca

8.09.  Canada - Supreme Court.

Domain:  dgbt.doc.ca
WWW:  http://debra.dgbt.doc.ca

8.10.  Canada - University of Montreal.

NAME AND ADDRESS:
University of Montreal
Daniel Poulin
Professor of Law and Computing Science

SHORT DESCRIPTION:
Sponsored by the University of Montreal and The Research Centre in Public Law 
(CRDP), this site includes decisions of Supreme Court of Canada since January 
1993.

Domain:  umontreal.ca
E-mail:  mailto:poulind@droit.umontreal.ca
WWW:  http://www.droit.umontreal.ca/english.html
Gopher:  gopher://gopher.droit.umontreal.ca/11/English

8.11.  Canada - West Coast Environmental Law Association.

