     (archived at http://www.law.cornell.edu/jol/jol.table.html and
     gopher://eagle.birds.wm.edu/11/MWSL/LJ/JoOL)

JPOL@shamash.nysernet.org (Jewish Political Discussion Mailing List)
     Send the following message to listproc@shamash.nysernet.org:
     subscribe jpol Your Name

JUDAFF-L@bingvmb.cc.binghamton.edu (Student Judicial Affairs Discussion List)
     Send the following message to listserv@bingvmb.cc.binghamton.edu or
     listserv@bingvmb.bitnet:
     subscribe judaff-l Your Name

JUDAISME-L@jer1.co.il (Forum francophone sur le Judaisme; discussion
of Judaism in French)
     Send the following message to listproc@jer1.co.il:
     subscribe judaisme-l <prenom> <nom>
     (was on listserv@jerusalem1.datasrv.co.il)

JUDGES-L@ubvm.cc.buffalo.edu ("judges" who cancel posts to Usenet
newsgroups that threaten to overload NetNews/Usenet)
     Send the following message to listserv@ubvm.cc.buffalo.edu or
     listserv@ubvm.bitnet:
     subscribe judges-l Your Name

JUR-DE@uni-bayreuth.de (Discussion forum on the law of Germany; messages 
preferably in German or English)
     Send the following message to jur-de-request@uni-bayreuth.de:
     subscribe <yourname>

JURINET-L@CC.UMontreal.CA (Moderated list of Research Centre in Public
Law; New Supreme Court of Canada decisions; Other new offerings on
CRDP'servers/ Liste moderee du Centre de recherche en droit public;
Nouvelles decisions de la Cour supreme du Canada; autres nouveautes
sur les serveurs du CRDP - list to inform interested people about
new additions to the servers (FTP, gopher, web) at the University of
Montreal Faculty of Law)
    Send the following message to listproc@cc.umontreal.ca:
    subscribe juriNet-L your name
 
JURINEWS (electronic dissemination of news summarizing current decisions - 
similar to headnotes or syllabi - announcing judicial appointments, 
retirements, etc., of the Federal Constitutional Court
(Bundesverfassungsgericht), Supreme Court (Bundesgerichtshof), Labor, and 
other courts of Germany; in German)
     http://

JURIST-L@nic.surfnet.nl (Lawyers inform Lawyers on networking=Juristen
informeren juristen over netwerkgebruik; discussion is in Dutch)
     Send the following message to listserv@nic.surfnet.NL or
     listserv@hearn.bitnet:
     subscribe jurist-L Yourfirstname Yourlastname

JURIX@nic.surfnet.nl (Discussielijst van stichting juridische
kennissystemen; legal knowledge-based systems)
     Send the following message to listserv@nic.surfnet.NL or
     listserv@hearn.bitnet:
     subscribe jurix Your Name
     (proceedings of the annual international conferences of JURIX on
     legal knowledge-based systems since 1988 are archived at:
     http://130.89.90.84/Jurix_web/home.html)

JUSTINFO (Justice Information Electronic Mailing List; electronic
newsletter of the National Criminal Justice Reference Service;
designed for criminal justice professionals to obtain accurate,
current, and useful criminal justice-related information)
     Send the following message to listproc@ncjrs.aspensys.com:
     subscribe justinfo yourname

JUVENILELAW-L@lawlib.wuacc.edu (Juvenile Law list)
     Send the following message to listserv@lawlib.wuacc.edu:
     subscribe juvenilelaw-l Your Name

JUVJUST (Juvenile Justice; electronic mailing list service of the
Office of Juvenile Justice and Delinquency Prevention (OJJDP) and the
