<H1>ELECTRONIC MAILING LISTS Q-T</H1>
<HR>

<PRE>
QI@abacus.oxy.edu (Queer Immigration; mailing list to facilitate
discussion of the effect of immigration policy on
gay/lesbian/bisexual/transgendered people and their allies)
     Send the following message to majordomo@abacus.oxy.edu:
     subscribe qi
     (related info at http://www.qrd.org/QRD/)

QUEERLAW@abacus.oxy.edu (list for discussion, analysis and promulgation of
queer legal theory and all other aspects of sexual orientation and the
law; for law professors, students, and others interested in how the
law affects, and is affected by, sexual minorities - lesbians, gay
men, bisexuals, transgendered folks, etc.)
     Send the following message to majordomo@abacus.oxy.edu:
     subscribe queerlaw
     (related info via blank e-mail message to info@qrd.org and at
     http://www.qrd.org/QRD/)

QUEERPLANET@abacus.oxy.edu (list devoted to organizing and networking
among international lesbian/gay/bisexual/transgendered/etc.
communities, including improving nondiscrimination on the basis of
sexual orientation worldwide; discussion of immigration, AIDS, etc.;
interaction between international queer organizations such as ILGA)
     Send the following message to majordomo@abacus.oxy.edu:
     subscribe queerplanet
     (was on majordomo@vector.casti.com)
     (related info at http://www.qrd.org/QRD/world/)

QUOTE-PAGE (list containing daily ranges of a number of commodity
futures; lists most actively traded commodities in the U.S.)
     Send the following message to listserv@pitstar.com:
     sub quote-page youre-mailaddress

RARE-LAWBOOKS@netcom.com (Meyer Boswell Books, American Antiquarian
Bookshop, searchable electronic catalogue of about 6,000 rare law
books in its inventory)
     For more information about the database and for searching
     instructions, send to rare-lawbooks@netcom.com, the message:
     help
     with the subject:
     help

REGO-L@pandora.sf.ca.us (Reinventing Government; making government
work better and cost less; procurement, regulatory systems,
environmental management, etc.)
     Send the following message to listserv@pandora.sf.ca.us:
     subscribe rego-l Your Name

REGS-L@albnydh2.bitnet (Title 10 Rules and Regulations)
     Send the following message to listserv@ALBNYDH2.bitnet:
     subscribe regs-L Your Name

REGULATIONS@cs.stanford.edu (mailing list for folks interested in the
formal representation of legal and regulatory information; contact
Michael R. Genesereth at genesereth@cs.stanford.edu for more
subscriptoin information)

RELIGIONLAW@grizzly.ucla.edu (Religion and the Law --U.S.-based list
for discussion of free exercise, the Establishment Clause, Religious
Freedom Restoration Act, equal protection, religious discrimination
and religious harassment under Title VII, etc.; for law professors and
lawyers who practice in the area; a listproc list)
     Send the following message to listserv@GRIZZLY.UCLA.edu:
     subscribe ReligionLaw yourfirstname yourlastname

REPUB-L@vm.marist.edu (Republican Politics)
     Send the following message to listserv@vm.marist.edu or
     listserv@marist.bitnet:
     subscribe repub-l Your Name

