<HEAD><TITLE>Essays by subject :   Law and Religion
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H1><IMG SRC="/GIFS/BOOK.GIF" ALIGN = MIDDLE>Essays by subject : Law and Religion
  </H1>

<LI><A HREF="gopher://gopher.law.warwick.ac.uk:70/00/ltc/publications/conferences/oxford/mking.txt">Religion into Law, Law into Religion :  the Construction of a Secular Identity for Islam</A> by Michael <STRONG>King</STRONG><I> 1993 .</I> Oxford Critical Legal Conference <I>  </I><HR>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.hamline.edu/~jlr/survey94.html">Survey of Trends and Developments on Religious Liberty in the Courts 1994</A> by Carl H. <STRONG>Esbeck</STRONG><I> 10 J Law & Relig 544-572 (1993-94).</I> The purpose of this survey is to note important case law developments in the state and lower federal courts concerning religious liberty. Purposely omitted are the widely reported United States Supreme Court opinions, as well as cases where the Supreme Court has granted review during the 1993-94 term. The focus here is on significant or interesting cases that may otherwise escape broad attention. Only the facts and rationale of each decision is summarized. No editorial comment on the merits of these cases is intended. <I>  </I><HR>
