<BODY   BGCOLOR="#ffffff">

<HEAD><title>Library</title></HEAD>



<CENTER><IMG  ALIGN=CENTER ALT="Sir Leon" SRC="leo.gif"> <IMG SRC="LIB.GIF"  ALIGN=MIDDLE>

</CENTER>



<CENTER>

<IMG SRC="BLUEBAR.GIF">

</CENTER>





<CENTER>
<H4><A HREF="#Catalogues & Databases">Catalogues & Databases</A> - 
<A HREF="ACC.HTM">Accessions List</A></H4>

</CENTER>



<P>


The Library is named after Sir Leon Radzinowicz, the first Director of the Institute (1959-1972) and Wolfson Professor of Criminology (1959-1973), and was founded in 1960.  It now houses the most comprehensive criminology collection in the United Kingdom and holds approximately 35,000 books, 15,000 pamphlets and subscribes to around 250 periodicals.  There are collections of historical books, reports, statistics, microforms and other non-book material.</P>

<P><B>Opening Hours</B><br><BR><i> In Full Term:</i><br>Monday to Thursday 9.00am-8.30pm<BR> Friday 9.00am-5.00pm<br><i>In Vacation:</i><br>Monday to Friday 9.00am-5.00pm<br> The library does not open at the weekend.</P>

<P><B>Admission</B><br><BR> The library is open to:
<UL>
<LI>students and staff of the Institute<br><LI>visitors to the Institute<br><LI>other members of the University<br><LI>others who may be admitted on application to the <a href="staff/KRARUP.HTM">librarian</a><br>

</UL>

All users are required to register at the library desk and those using the library in the evening must sign the invigilator's record book.</P></BODY>

<b><A NAME="Catalogues & Databases">Catalogues & Databases</A></b><P>



The Radzinowicz Library catalogue can be accessed by telnet connection to the <A HREF="telnet://ul.cam.ac.uk/">Cambridge University Library Catalogue</A>.  When connected select Departmental and College Libraries (option 3), then select the Radzinowicz Library as the preferred library (option 6, then '33').

<BR><BR>

The Telnet address is <I>ul.cam.ac.uk</I><BR>

<BR>

<B>Links to other Catalogues and Databases</B>

<UL>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.cam.ac.uk/Libraries/">Cambridge University Library</A>

<LI><A HREF="http://portico.bl.uk/">British Library</A>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.niss.ac.uk/reference/index.html">NISS Information Gateway</A>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.cam.ac.uk/Hytelnet/index.html">Hytelnet link to library catalogues worldwide</A>

<LI><A HREF="telnet://locis.loc.gov/">Library of Congress</A>

<LI><A HREF="telnet://bids.ac.uk/">BIDS</A>

<LI><A HREF="telnet://wwwx25.niss.ac.uk:20014/">First Search</A>  -  online reference service from OCLC.  Supports over 50 databases including OCLC's WorldCat, Article First and Medline.<BR>  

<LI><A HREF="http://curlopac.ac.uk/curlinfo/">CURL</A> - 8.6 million records
from the Consortium of Research Libraries.
</UL>

<P>Both BIDS and First Search require passwords.  Please see the librarian for details.

Access to some of the above catalogues require you to have configured your browser to allow telnet connections.</P>

