<HTML>
<BODY  BGCOLOR="#ffffff"> <TITLE>Inter-Departmental Ph.D. Workshop Programme 1996-1997</TITLE>
<IMG Align=left SRC="CAM2.GIF">
<CENTER>
<H1>Inter-Departmental Ph.D. Workshops 1996-1997</H1>
</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="BLUEBAR.GIF" ALT="bar">
</CENTER>
<BR>

<P>The workshops are open to all Ph.D. students and reseach staff in the Institute of Criminology, the Faculty of Law, the Faculty of Social and Political Sciences, and the Departments of Education, Social Anthropolgy, and Geography.</P>

<P><A HREF="INTDEP1.HTM">Workshop Objectives</A></P>
<P><A HREF="INTDEP2.HTM">Workshop Timetable 1996-97</A></P>

<STRONG>Registration
</STRONG>

<P>If you would like to attend any of the workshops please contact Justina Molloy at the addess below with your name, college, department and email address:-</P>
 
<ul><STRONG>Justina Molloy - Institute of Criminology (use UMS)<BR>
Email: jem1013@cam.ac.uk<BR>
Tel: 335372</STRONG></ul>

<P>Places are allocated on a strict first come, first served basis, but there is some flexibility re: workshop numbers.  Please note that this is a rolling programme.  Block bookings will be accepted for each term but <STRONG>not</STRONG> for the whole academic year.</P>

<P>There is an Inter-Departmental Ph.D. Workshop mailing list at crim-phd@lists.cam.ac.uk.  Email addresses of participants will be posted there.  Please check your email regularly for confirmation of places, venues, times, etc.  IF YOU WISH TO POST SOMETHING TO THE MAILING LIST PLEASE ENSURE THAT IT IS RELEVANT TO EVERYONE ATTENDING THE WORKSHOPS!
</P>
<P>For further information contact Loraine Gelsthorpe (Criminology, Tel:  335377 or
338148 Email:  lrg10@cam.ac.uk) or Jackie Scott (SPS, Tel:  334558 or 335610 
Email:  jls1004@cam.ac.uk)

</P>


</body>
</html>
