ele University)<P><li> <A HREF="RESEARCH/F4&.HTM">The Wolds Private Prison: An Analysis</A> (Professor Keith Bottomley and Mr Adrian James, Hull University, with Dr Alison Liebling)<P><li> <A HREF="RESEARCH/F6&.HTM">Vulnerability, Custody and Incentive-Based Regimes for Offenders</A> (Dr Alison Liebling, Economic and Social Research Council Post-Doctoral Fellowship)<P></ul><A NAME="mental"><hr><H3>Mentally Abnormal Offenders</H3><P><ul><li> <A HREF="RESEARCH/G1&.HTM">The Supervision of Restricted Patients</A> (Mrs Susanne Dell and Dr Adrian Grounds)<P><li> <A HREF="RESEARCH/G2&.HTM">A Critical Review of Understandings of the Mentally Disordered Offender in the Penal System</A> (Dr Adrian Grounds)<P></ul><P><A NAME="victims"><HR><h3>Crime and Victimisation</H3></P><p><ul><li> <A HREF="research/h3.htm">The Nature and Extent of Domestic Violence in Cambridge</A> (Dr Loraine Gelsthorpe and Amanda Matravers)<P></ul><P><ul><li>  <A HREF="research/h1.htm">National Crime and Community Safety Survey in the Cayman Islands</A>  (Dr Kate Painter) </P><P><li> <A HREF="research/h2.htm"> An Investigation into Violence Within Marriage</A>  (Dr Kate Painter)</P><a name="drugs"></ul>

