<HTML><BODY  BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><HEAD><title>Prof. Bottoms</title><h1><IMG ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE  ALT="crest" SRC="CAM2.GIF" > Professor Anthony Bottoms</h1><CENTER><IMG SRC="BLUEBAR.GIF"></CENTER></HEAD><BR><P>Wolfson Professor of Criminology, Director of the Institute of Criminology and Fellow of Fitzwilliam College.</P><P>Professor Bottoms' main research interests lie in the fields of criminal justice policy and environmental criminology, and he has conducted empirical research on a wide range of topics including imprisonment, non-custodial penalties, and urban crime patterns.  His publications include <I>The Urban Criminal</I> (1976), <I>Defendants in the Criminal Process</I> (1976), <I>The Coming Penal Crisis</I> (1980), <I>Problems of Long-Term Imprisonment</I> (1987), <I>Intermediate Treatment and Juvenile Justice</I> (1990), and <I>Prisons and the Problem of Order</I> (1996).</P><HR><P>Institute of Criminology<BR>University of Cambridge<BR>7 West Road<BR>Cambridge<BR>England<BR>CB3  9DT<BR><BR>Tel:  +44 1223 335360<BR>Director's Secretary: +44 1223 335369<BR>Fax: +44 1223 335356<BR></P></BODY></HEAD>
</DOC>
