<HTML><BODY  BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><HEAD><TITLE>Professor  David Farrington</TITLE><H1><IMG ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE  ALT="crest" SRC="CAM2.GIF" > Professor  David Farrington</H1><CENTER><IMG SRC="BLUEBAR.GIF"></CENTER></HEAD><BR><P>Professor of Psychological Criminology</P><P> Professor Farrington is a psychologist whose interests focus particularly upon longitudinal studies of criminal careers. He is the director of the Cambridge Study in Delinquent Development, a long-term follow-up of 400 males first studied by Professor D.J. West in the 1960s. In addition to many research papers arising from the Cambridge Study, Professor Farrington has published widely on other topics, including methodological issues, comparative criminology, and the composition of recorded crime rates. His books include <I>The Delinquent Way of Life</I> (1977), <I>Prediction in Criminology</I> (1985), <I>Understanding and Controlling Crime</I> (1986) and <I>Human Development and Criminal Behaviour</I> (1991).  Professor Farrington is a past President of the British Society of Criminology.</P><HR><P>Institute of Criminology<BR>University of Cambridge<BR>7 West Road<BR>Cambridge<BR>England<BR>CB3  9DT<BR><BR>Tel:  +44 1223 335360<BR>Direct line: +44 1223 335384<BR>Fax: +44 1223 335356<BR></P></BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
