<HTML><BODY    BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><HEAD><TITLE>Recent Research</TITLE></HEAD><H1><IMG ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE  ALT="crest" SRC="CAM2.GIF" ><B>Recent Research</B></H1><BODY><CENTER><IMG SRC="BLUEBAR.GIF"></CENTER><H2>Research Project</H2><h3>Inter-agency Aspects of Crime Prevention (Dr Loraine Gelsthorpe and Mark Liddle)</h3><P>This research project, funded by the Home Office Crime Prevention Unit, aimed to describe and compare the organisational structures and strategies used in the delivery of services by multi-agency crime prevention schemes, and to explore what makes for good inter-agency co-operation (or indeed, its opposite) and good service delivery in different types of scheme. More specifically, the research sought to estimate the effectiveness of different agencies (police, probation, local authorities, Crime Concern, the Home Office itself and any other agency, voluntary or statutory, involved in the scheme) in terms of:a) stimulating and implementing crime prevention b) organising and sustaining a multi-agency structure c) establishing and monitoring local schemes and projects.The findings of the study have recently been published in three Home Office Crime Prevention Unit booklets.</P>
</DOC>
<DOC>
