<HTML><BODY    BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><HEAD><TITLE>Recent Research</TITLE></HEAD><H1><IMG ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE  ALT="crest" SRC="CAM2.GIF" ><B>Recent Research</B></H1><BODY><CENTER><IMG SRC="BLUEBAR.GIF"></CENTER><H2>Research Project</H2><H3>An Investigation into the Effect of Environmental Cues on Offender Decision Making: The Case of Burglary and Vehicle Crime <BR>(Dr. Kate Painter)</H3><P>The research is a produce of a multi-agency programme involving probation, social services, and the police in the London Borough of Redbridge.  The aim of the survey is to interview a sample of local offenders currently involved with probation, social services, or the police and to ask them about the effect of environmental cues on their decisions to offend.  The research will focus on burglary and vehicle crime and will use a range of data-gathering methods, including use of photographs, on-the-street observation, and crime mapping.</P></body></html>
</DOC>
