<TITLE>Bennett - Contents</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<DL>
<DD>
<dd><H4><CITE><A HREF="books.HTM">Preventing Crime and Disorder:  Targeting Strategies and Responibilites</A></CITE> - Edited by Trevor Bennett</cite></h4>
<dd><H3>Contents</H3>
<DD>
<DD><STRONG>Part 1 - Perspectives on Crime Prevention</STRONG><BR><BR>
<DD><STRONG>1</STRONG><CITE> Understanding Crime Prevention in Late Modern Societies</CITE> - Anthony Bottoms and Paul Wiles
<DD><STRONG>2</STRONG><CITE> Towards a Discipline of Crime Prevention:  A Systematic Approach to its Nature, Range and Concepts</CITE> - Paul Ekblom
<DD><STRONG>3</STRONG><CITE> Roles and Responsibilities in the Prevention of Crime</CITE> - Gloria Laycock
<DD><STRONG>4</STRONG><CITE> Urban Neighbourhoods and Crime Prevention Strategies</CITE> - Per-Olof Wikstrom
<DD><BR>
<DD><STRONG>Part 2 - Community Organisation and Change</STRONG><BR><BR>
<DD><STRONG>5</STRONG><CITE> Local Safety and Democracy</CITE> - Edward Chambers
<DD><STRONG>6</STRONG> <CITE>Communities, Crime and Equality in England and Wales</CITE> - Timothy Hope
<DD><STRONG>7</STRONG><CITE> Organised against Crime:  Approaches to Lawlessness in Bristol</CITE> - Neil Jameson and Peter Stokes
<DD><BR>
<DD><STRONG>Part 3 - Community Policing and Defence</STRONG><BR><BR>
<DD><STRONG>8</STRONG><CITE> Private Policing, Vigilance and Vigilantism:  Commercialisation and Citizenship as Crime Prevention Strategies</CITE> - Les Johnston
<DD><STRONG>9</STRONG><CITE> Partnerships for Prevention?  Some Obstacles to Police-Community Co-operation</CITE> - Wesley Skogan
<DD> <BR>
<DD><STRONG>Part 4 - Targeting Offences, Offenders, Victims, and Places</STRONG><BR><BR>
<DD><STRONG>10</STRONG><CITE> Problem-Solving Policing and Crime Prevention:  An Assessment of the Role of the Police in Preventing Crime</CITE> - Trevor Bennett
<DD><STRONG>11</STRONG><CITE> High Crime Rates, Repeat Victimisation, and Routine Activities </CITE>- Ken Pease and Graham Farrell
<DD><BR>
<DD><STRONG>Part 5 - Targeting Estates and Residential Areas</STRONG><BR><BR>
<DD><STRONG>12</STRONG><CITE> Reflections on the Effectiveness of Estate Improvement Programmes</CITE> - Steve Osborn
<DD><STRONG>13</STRONG> <CITE>Street Lighting, Crime, Disorder and Fear:  A Review of the Research in the United Kingdom</CITE> - Kate Painter
<DD><STRONG>14</STRONG><CITE> Targeted Crime Reduction:  The Needs of Local Groups</CITE> - Joanna Shapland
<DD><BR>
<DD><STRONG>Part 6 - Targeting Young People and Potential Offenders</STRONG><BR><BR>
<DD><STRONG>15</STRONG><CITE> Preventing Youth Crime in High-Crime Areas:  Towards a Strategy</CITE> - Jon Bright
<DD><STRONG>16</STRONG><CITE> Families, Schools and Criminality Prevention</CITE> - John Graham and David Utting
<DD><STRONG>17</STRONG><CITE> High/Scope-High Hopes:  An Early Childhood Intervention Programme</CITE> - Joan Santer

</DL>
</BODY>
