<HTML>

<BODY  BGCOLOR="#ffffff"> <TITLE>Inter-Departmental Ph.D. Workshop Objectives</TITLE>
<IMG Align=left SRC="CAM2.GIF">
<CENTER>
<H1>Inter-Departmental Ph.D. Workshop Objectives</H1>
</CENTER>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="BLUEBAR.GIF" ALT="bar">
</CENTER>
<BR>
			
<P>This Programme involves a series of workshops designed to cover a broad range of practical topics that will help students in the research process, from getting started and formulating researchable questions through to writing the dissertation and preparing and giving papers.  The workshops have several leaders and students are encouraged to participate through a variety of practical exercises.  The workshop sequence covers four phases of the research process.  First there is a workshop devoted to students own Ph.D. topics which aims to draw out common concerns, dilemmas, and unresolved issues that materialise when translating ideas into reseach action.  Second, several workshops are devoted to different methods of data collection.  Further workshops are devoted to bibliographic searches, accessing secondary data sources and the use of archives in research.  Third there are workshops designed to highlight some of the important considerations of qualitative and quantitative data analysis and to give students a greater understanding of some of the tools at their disposal, for example, computer assisted qualitative analysis.  Finally two workshops are devoted to writing skills and preparing and giving papers.</P>
</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
