<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>TASSP Information </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="image51.gif" WIDTH="392" HEIGHT="54" ALIGN=bottom 
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR>
<A HREF="about.htm"><IMG SRC="image44.gif" WIDTH="197" HEIGHT="44" ALIGN=
bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" BORDER="0"></A></CENTER>
<P>The Texas Association of Secondary School Principals was established
in 1922 as a department of the state teachers' organization. Its purpose
was (and is) to offer Texas principals a forum to explore the best practices
in school administration with the ultimate goal of helping facilitate student
learning. <BR>
<BR>
All TASSP policies are created by the <A HREF="office2.htm">TASSP Board
of Directors.</A> The Board is made up of principals and assistant principals
from each of the 20 TASSP Regions. TASSP policy is driven by the mission
statement and goals adopted by the Board.<BR>
<BR>
The TASSP <B>mission</B> is to provide proactive leadership to systemically
change schools into learning communities in which all students and other
participants achieve their full potential as lifelong learners in a diverse
and changing society. <BR>
<BR>
The seven TASSP <B>goals</B> are as follows: 
<UL>
<LI>Confront the reality of and strategies for systemic change. 
<LI>Provide a framework to radically change curriculum and instruction to
meet real world needs. 
<LI>Equip professionals with knowledge and skills needed to provide leadership
for schools of the 21st century. 
<LI>Exert a strong political presence in all matters affecting secondary
education. 
<LI>Enhance collegial support systems. 
<LI>Foster and support student leadership opportunities. 
<LI>Develop and maintain a full range of membership services. 
</UL>
<P><CENTER><BR>
For more information, you may contact any of the <A HREF="staff.htm">staff</A>
at:<BR>
<BR>
TASSP<BR>
1833 South IH 35<BR>
Austin, TX 78741-3799<BR>
512 / 443-2100<BR>
fax: 512 / 442-3343<BR>
e-mail: <A HREF="mailto:jshaddix@tassp.org">jshaddix@tassp.org</A><BR>
<BR>
For further information on membership, click <A HREF="meminfo.htm">here<BR>
<BR>
</A><A HREF="mainmenu.htm"><IMG SRC="image230.gif" WIDTH="54" HEIGHT="42"
ALIGN=middle NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" BORDER="0"></A>Click icon or <A HREF="mainmenu.htm">here</A>
to return to Main Menu<BR>
