<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Professional Development Opportunities</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="image51.gif" WIDTH="392" HEIGHT="54" ALIGN=bottom 
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR>
<IMG SRC="image146.gif" WIDTH="195" HEIGHT="44" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"><IMG SRC="image43.gif" WIDTH="197" HEIGHT="44" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"><BR>
<BR>
<IMG SRC="image232.gif" WIDTH="104" HEIGHT="63" ALIGN=middle NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"><BR>
<BR>
Each June the TASSP Summer Workshop is held in Austin. Featuring nationally
known speakers and distinguished educators on the program, this workshop
is an important event for secondary campus leaders. It is also the time
when TASSP business affairs are conducted. </CENTER>
<P>
<P><CENTER><B>Next scheduled date: June 11-13, 1997<BR>
<BR>
</B><BR>
<IMG SRC="image233.gif" WIDTH="81" HEIGHT="61" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"><BR>
<BR>
The <B>Assistant Principal Leadership Conference</B> is held in February.
This workshop is an invaluable source of information on both legal and practical
administrative matters for all high school and middle level assistant principals.</CENTER>
<P>
<P><CENTER><B>Next scheduled date: February 8-10, 1997<BR>
<BR>
</B><BR>
<IMG SRC="image235.gif" WIDTH="81" HEIGHT="73" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"><BR>
<BR>
The <A HREF="natcon.htm">National Conference of Texas</A>, in October each
year, is attended by thousands of educators. This unique team conference
brings together both teachers and administrators from Pre-K through Secondary
levels for the purpose of improving teaching and learning. </CENTER>
<P>
<P><CENTER><B>Next scheduled date: October 26-28, 1996<BR>
