<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Recognition Programs</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="image51.gif" WIDTH="392" HEIGHT="54" ALIGN=bottom 
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR>
<IMG SRC="image146.gif" WIDTH="195" HEIGHT="44" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"><IMG SRC="image227.gif" WIDTH="197" HEIGHT="44" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"></CENTER>
<P>TASSP RECOGNITION PROGRAMS<BR>
<BR>
<I><STRONG>Administrative Awards</STRONG></I><BR>
<BR>
Every year TASSP recognizes superior work by high school and middle level
administrators with its Outstanding Principal Awards.<BR>
<BR>
In each of the 20 TASSP regions, an Outstanding High School Principal and
Assistant Principal and an Outstanding Junior High/Middle Level Principal
and Assistant Principal are chosen. These administrators are recognized
at the TASSP Summer Workshop in June, and are encouraged to apply for the
corresponding national awards: the NASSP/Met Life Principal of the Year
Award and the NASSP/McDonald's Assistant Principal of the Year.<BR>
<BR>
<I><STRONG>Student Awards</STRONG></I><BR>
<BR>
In an attempt to encourage scholastic achievement by high school students,
TASSP asks member principals to select outstanding graduating seniors for
nomination for the All-State Academic Team. A state selection committee
utilizes a comprehensive process to choose a twenty-member All-State Academic
Team From the local nominees. The Team is chosen based on grades, strength
of curriculum path, SAT/ACT scores, and a student-generated essay on a topic
related to school experience. <BR>
<BR>
Each member of the Team is invited to attend the June Summer Workshop and
is awarded a $500 unrestricted scholarship in recognition of his/her efforts.
<BR>
<P><CENTER><STRONG>Back to <A HREF="member.htm">Member Services</A>.<BR>
